
Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I go to Page 05 of Elbow MRI

When I select 'Finding' radio button
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Ligaments' from the dropdown menu
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Medial collateral ligament tear' radio button is enabled
And 'Lateral collateral ligament tear' radio button is enabled
And 'Dislocation with lesions of MCL and LCL' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Medial collateral ligament tear' radio button
Then 'Anterior bundle (AMCL)' checkbox is enabled
And 'Posterior bundle (PMCL)' checkbox is enabled
And 'Transversal bundle "Cooper's ligament"' checkbox is enabled
And 'Lesion of the pronator-flexor tendon complex' checkbox is enabled

And 'Complete tear' radio button is enabled
And 'Partial tear' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Complete tear' radio button
Then 'Localization' checkbox is enabled
And 'Retraction' checkbox is enabled
And 'Adjacent soft tissue edema' checkbox is enabled
And 'Concomitant injuries of the adjacent muscle/enthesis' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Localization' checkbox
Then 'Proximal' radio button is enabled
And 'Distal' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Partial tear' radio button
Then 'Ill-defined margin' checkbox is enabled
And 'Increased signal' checkbox is enabled
And 'Thickening' checkbox is enabled
And 'T-Sign' checkbox is enabled
And 'Wavy appearance' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Thickening' checkbox
Then '> 4 mm diameter (in medial portion)' checkbox is enabled
